            <thetext>&quot;pointerEvents&quot; in document.documentElement.style returns true. However elements with styles.pointerEvents = &quot;none&quot; still fire mouse events. This means that protector elements are required for all versions of Opera.

When this browser issue is fixed, the browser switch in qx.bom.client.Feature targeting Opera can be restricted to buggy versions.

This bug is also related to bug #4099.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
